---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for Winback Campaigns in 2026';
const description = 'A practical guide to Shopify email apps for winback campaigns, covering cohort logic, suppression, product relevance, pricing context, sources, and tradeoffs.';
const apps = [
['Sequenzy','Lean teams with clear reactivation sequences','Focused lifecycle workflows','Less advanced cohort analysis should be checked','https://sequenzy.com','Start with one genuinely inactive cohort and a non-discount reason to return, such as education, a new collection, or a relevant replenishment note. Exclude recent buyers and open service cases before testing.'],
['Klaviyo','Detailed recency and product-behavior cohorts','Flexible event and predictive segmentation','Requires careful frequency and data governance','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation','Klaviyo fits stores where inactivity varies by product interval and customer behavior. Define recency relative to the product, not one global number, and make suppression rules easy to inspect.'],
['Omnisend','Retail reactivation across email and SMS','Accessible campaign automation','Discount pressure can become the default','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/','Omnisend is practical for a coordinated reactivation campaign. Keep the first message useful and reserve discounts for a tested segment rather than making price reduction the default reason to return.'],
['Drip','DTC stores analyzing repeat-purchase behavior','Commerce automation and revenue reporting','May exceed a small store’s needs','https://www.drip.com/features','Drip suits winback programs tied to repeat-purchase timing. Compare targeted and holdout cohorts by incremental orders, margin, returns, and unsubscribes.'],
['Brevo','Broad lifecycle and transactional coverage','Email and contact-oriented options','More manual ecommerce cohort modeling','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/','Brevo can support lifecycle reactivation beside operational messages. Keep service and marketing streams separate and make the inactivity rule explicit in the audience definition.'],
['Shopify Email','Small stores sending a simple reactivation note','Native campaign and customer setup','Limited cohort and holdout logic','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing','Shopify Email is a good starting point for a small audience and a clear product story. Track a comparison group outside the platform if the team wants to judge incremental effect.'],
['Mailchimp','Editorial brands re-engaging newsletter readers','Campaigns, audiences, and content workflows','Advanced product inactivity logic needs design','https://mailchimp.com/features/email/','Mailchimp fits a content-led winback where the reason to return is a guide, story, or new collection. Do not treat an old click as proof that a subscriber wants indefinite promotion.'],
['Customer.io','Technical stores with product and service events','Flexible event-triggered messaging','Engineering and QA effort are substantial','https://customer.io/product/messaging/','Customer.io is useful when activity, support, and purchase events define inactivity. Add event timestamps and exclusions so a delayed event does not resurrect a customer who just bought.'],
['ActiveCampaign','Winback connected to CRM and lifecycle stages','Automation and contact segmentation','Cross-team ownership is demanding','https://www.activecampaign.com/marketing-automation','ActiveCampaign suits stores where reactivation depends on account or membership context. Keep service notes and marketing permission separate, and document the exit after purchase.'],
['MailerLite','Small lists with a simple reactivation path','Accessible campaigns and basic automation','Limited fit for many product cohorts','https://www.mailerlite.com/features','MailerLite is a sensible low-overhead choice for one reactivation audience. Its simplicity can help a small team test cadence and content without building a large automation tree.'],
['ConvertKit','Creator-led brands re-engaging through education','Subscriber sequences and broadcasts','Commerce cohort depth is limited','https://convertkit.com/features','ConvertKit works when a subscriber may return for a lesson, story, or creator recommendation. Make the content useful without requiring a discount and keep commerce attribution modest.'],
['GetResponse','Winback paired with events or landing pages','Automation, landing pages, and event tools','Broader suite adds operating overhead','https://www.getresponse.com/features','GetResponse fits a reactivation program built around a guide, webinar, or launch page. Separate attendees, purchasers, and inactive subscribers before sending a second follow-up.'],
['HubSpot','Reactivation coordinated with sales and service','CRM-connected marketing and subscription context','Cost and administration can be substantial','https://www.hubspot.com/products/marketing','HubSpot makes sense when winback depends on account, service, or sales context. Define ownership and subscription types before putting a dormant CRM record into marketing automation.']
];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">A winback campaign should answer why a customer might return, not simply announce another discount. Timing, product relevance, service history, and consent determine whether reactivation feels useful or intrusive.</p><p>We prioritize cohort definition, purchase suppression, product relevance, and holdout-friendly measurement. Confirm current pricing and use a baseline cohort before making claims about performance.</p><h2>Shortlist for reactivation</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for winback campaigns</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[5]}</p><p><strong>Pros:</strong> {a[2]}. <strong>Cons:</strong> {a[3]}. <strong>Pricing:</strong> verify official plans for contacts, sends, seats, SMS, reporting, support, and implementation at the <a href={a[4]} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official source</a>. Pilot one inactive cohort against a baseline or holdout and compare incremental orders, margin, unsubscribes, complaints, and support impact.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros in practice</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Risk to manage</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Evidence to review</th><td>Inactivity definition, suppression, reason to return, holdout behavior, incremental orders, margin, and unsubscribes.</td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Winback priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Lean reactivation sequence</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Focused lifecycle operations.</td></tr><tr><td>Detailed recency and product cohorts</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible event segmentation.</td></tr><tr><td>Commerce retention reporting</td><td>Drip</td><td>Repeat-purchase orientation.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Continue with the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/use-cases/winback">winback guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
